2500|$|In April 2016, Heard {{appeared}} in the Southport Magistrates Court and pleaded guilty to falsifying quarantine documents, stating that she was sleep deprived and made a mistake. The two <b>biosecurity</b> charges were dropped, and she was placed on a one-month good behaviour bond, paying a $1,000 fine for producing a false document. Heard and Depp also released a video in which they apologized for their behavior and urged people {{to adhere to the}} <b>biosecurity</b> laws. The Guardian called the case the [...] "highest profile criminal quarantine case" [...] in Australian history.|$|E
